{"word":"ἐπίληπτος","slug":"ἐπίληπτος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπίληπτος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐπιλαμβάνω'><el>ἐπιλαμβάνω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>caught</i> or <i>detected in</i> anything, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a>, <el>ἐπίλαμπτος ἀφάσσουσα</el> <i>caught</i> in the act of feeling, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>suffering</i>, <b><a href='S:Demosthenes'>Dem.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}